-- Equatorial Guinea's President Says No Public Funds Transferred Overseas
-- Mike Cohen
-- 2010-06-28T12:08:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/equatorial-guinea-s-president-says-no-public-funds-transferred-overseas.html

          
          
             Equatorial Guinea’s President
Teodoro Obiang Nguema Mbasogo said there have been no public
funds transferred abroad and information of corruption in the
country is “incorrect.”  
 No complaints have been received about the voters roll in
recent elections, Obiang said at the Fortune Global Forum in
Cape Town today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
